{"title":"Archonstorm","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Archonstorm","type":"markdown","data":"**\"Archonstorm\"** is a nickname given to a situation in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")* where a player ends up facing a large group of [Archons](/wiki/Archon \"Archon\").\n\n## Description\n\n*The following information pertains to an upcoming version ([NetHack 3.7.0](/wiki/NetHack_3.7.0 \"NetHack 3.7.0\")). If this version is now released, please verify that it is still accurate, then update the page to incorporate this information.*\n\nSummon nasties can no longer create monsters of equal or higher difficulty than the caster (preventing, e.g., arch-liches or Archons from summoning more of themselves).\n\nWhile Archons are formidable foes all on their own, a disproportionate number may spawn if the player has [genocided](/wiki/Genocide \"Genocide\") several other high-level monsters; the Archon is also more liable to summon another Archon via the [summon nasties](/wiki/Summon_nasties \"Summon nasties\") spell as a result. In a worst-case scenario, this can become a chain of summons that grows exponentially and fills most of the level with Archons. This usually occurs on the [Elemental Planes](/wiki/Elemental_Planes \"Elemental Planes\") in the [endgame](/wiki/Endgame \"Endgame\"), but is most commonly seen on the [Plane of Fire](/wiki/Plane_of_Fire \"Plane of Fire\"), as it is the most open of the eligible levels; it also occasionally happens on the [Plane of Air](/wiki/Plane_of_Air \"Plane of Air\"), and very rarely on other planes.\n\n## Strategy\n\nThe player caught in an Archonstorm is likely doomed: even if they have a means of driving off the Archons and gaining breathing room, they are very likely to be swarmed and surrounded by the other Archons and remaining nasties. [Conflict](/wiki/Conflict \"Conflict\") may or may not have any effect due to the Archons' [monster magic resistance](/wiki/Monster_magic_resistance \"Monster magic resistance\"), and unless your AC is incredibly high, you may be struck down before you can get clear of them. As such, Archonstorms in particular are a major reason why it is discouraged to perform excessive genociding of monsters.\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.](/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Archonstorm - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Archonstorm\",\"wgTitle\":\"Archonstorm\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":150236,\"wgRevisionId\":150236,\"wgArticleId\":23980,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Upcoming\",\"Nethack-366 articles\",\"Strategy\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Archonstorm\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":23980,\"wgRequestId\":\"6d2100c34ca025803bfe39c7\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEdit